al\">{{cite web | title = Young man convicted in Foss High School shooting sentenced to prison | publisher = The News Tribune | date = June 5, 2009 | url = http://blog.thenewstribune.com/crime/2009/06/05/young-man-convicted-in-foss-high-school-shooting-sentenced-to-prison/ | first = Adam | last = Lynn | accessdate = May 21, 2013 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140226021748/http://blog.thenewstribune.com/crime/2009/06/05/young-man-convicted-in-foss-high-school-shooting-sentenced-to-prison/ | archive-date = February 26, 2014 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| January 19, 2007\n| [[Sudbury, Massachusetts]], United States\n| John Odgren, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old James Alenson was [[n:Stabbing at Massachusetts high school leaves one dead|stabbed to death with a knife in the Lincoln-Sudbury Regional High School washroom]] in the East House section by 16-year-old John Odgren. Odgren did not know Alenson, and he chose to stab him at random. In 2010, Odgren was found guilty of first-degree murder and was sentenced to life without parole.<ref>\"[http://www.metrowestdailynews.com/homepage/8998993118795661308 'I did it ... I did it': Student suspect in deadly stabbing is held without bail]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\", ''The MetroWest Daily News'', January 19, 2007. Retrieved January 19, 2007.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/10792195/detail.html |title=Teen Charged In Fellow Student's Death Freshman Stabbed To Death In High School |date=January 19, 2007 |work=WCVB-TV |accessdate=2009-10-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090602220401/http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/10792195/detail.html |archivedate=June 2, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thebostonchannel.com/news/21313592/detail.html |title=Judge OK's Teen's Jailhouse Tapes In Stab Case Prosecutors Challenging Whether Odgren Was Legally Insane |date=October 16, 2009 |work=WCVB-TV |accessda