068%2C00.html |archivedate=November 2, 2008 }}</ref>\n|-\n| October 16, 2008\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| William Morton, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| Christopher Walker, 16, was killed, and three other teenagers were seriously wounded during a drive-by shooting at a primary school lawn adjacent to [[Henry Ford High School (Detroit, Michigan)|Henry Ford High School]], where Walker and the other students were just dismissed from after classes ended. Three teenagers were arrested and charged in connection with the shooting.<ref name=\"foxnewsdetroit\">{{cite news|title=Teen Killed in Shooting Near Detroit High School|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,439563,00.html|work=[[FOX News]]|date=October 16, 2008|accessdate=September 5, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309044022/http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,439563,00.html|archive-date=2009-03-09|url-status=dead}}</ref> William Morton, 15, the shooter, was sentenced to life without parole, and Devon Bell was sentenced to 42 years of prison.<ref>{{cite news|title=PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN vs. WILLIAM MORTON / PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN vs. DEVON BELL|url =http://statecasefiles.justia.com/documents/michigan/court-of-appeals-unpublished/294823.pdf?ts=1337947679|publisher=State of Michigan|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate = September 5, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| October 31, 2008\n| [[Stockton Springs]],<br>[[Maine]],<br>United States\n| Randall Hofland, 55\n|\n|\n| Eleven fifth-grade students were taken hostage in a classroom at Stockton Springs Elementary School, in [[Stockton Springs]], [[Maine]]. The hostage situation ended within 30 minutes when the gunman surrendered to a [[state trooper]]. The hostage taker, 55-year-old Randall Hofland, was wanted by authorities for pointing a handgun at an officer during a traffic stop and then fleeing.<ref name=\"maine1031\">{{cite news|title=Maine Gunman Held Fifth-Graders Hostage|date=2008-10-31|publisher=CBS News|url =http://www.cbsnews.co