e.com/news/local/2010-10-24/tpd_investigates_homicide |title=TPD investigates homicide |publisher=Cjonline.com |date=2010-10-24 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 29, 2010\n| [[Marinette, Wisconsin|Marinette]],<br>[[Wisconsin]],<br>United States\n| Samuel Hengel, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Samuel Hengel took 23 students and one teacher hostage for over 5 hours at Marinette High School after firing shots at a projector. The suspect, a student in the sophomore Western Civilization class, shot himself after police officers stormed the classroom shortly after 8 p.m. All hostages were removed safely. Hengel died at 10:44 the next morning<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ehextra.com/main.asp?SectionID=12&SubSectionID=35&ArticleID=9048 |title=Teen dies \u2013 EHEXTRA \u2013 Marinette, WI |publisher=Ehextra |date=2010-12-01 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ehextra.com/main.asp?SectionID=12&SubSectionID=35&ArticleID=9043 |title=Students safe \u2013 EHEXTRA \u2013 Marinette, WI |publisher=Ehextra |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 6, 2010\n| [[Aurora, Colorado]], United States\n| Luis Enrique Guzman-Rincon, 20\n|\n| 1 injured\n| In a gang-related attack outside [[Aurora Central High School]], a 17-year-old girl was shot and wounded. The wounds caused her to be paralyzed. Luis Enrique Guzman-Rincon, 20, fired shots from a car while students were standing outside the high school, trying to shoot at a group of students who were believed to be gang rivals. Guzman-Ricon was sentenced to 35 years in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_21936390/gang-member-gets-35-years-2010-shooting-at |title=Gang member gets 35 years for 2010 shooting at Aurora high school|newspaper=[[The Denver Post]] |date=November 6, 2012 |accessdate=January 15, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 14, 2010\n| [[Panama City, Florida|Panama City]],<br>[[Florida]],<br>United States\n| Clay Duke, 56\n| 1 dead\n|\n| [[2010 Panama City school board shootings]]. A g