ex.html|title=Kentucky school shooting: 2 students killed, 18 injured|author1=Holly Yan |author2=AnneClaire Stapleton |author3=Paul P. Murphy|website=cnn.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|February 14, 2018}}\n|[[Parkland, Florida]], US\n| Nikolas Cruz, 19\n| 17 dead\n| 17 injured\n|[[Stoneman Douglas High School shooting]]\n|-\n|-\n|{{Dts|March 20,2018}}\n|[[Great Mills, Maryland]], US\n| Austin Rollins, 17\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 17-year-old male student, armed with a handgun, shot and fatally injured a female student (with whom he had a prior relationship), then began firing at random people in the school, wounding a male student. The student shot himself in the head, fatally, while the school resource officer simultaneously shot at him.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.southernmarylandchronicle.com/2018/03/26/smcso-releases-timeline-of-great-mills-high-school-shooting/|title=SMCSO releases timeline of Great Mills High School shooting |date=March 26, 2018 |work=TheSouthernMarylanChronicle}}</ref> \n|-\n|{{Dts|March 21, 2018}}\n|[[Shadrinsk]], Russia\n| Student, 13\n|\n| 7 injured\n| A 13-year-old girl opened fire with a gas pistol at her school in Russia's Kurgan region, injuring seven seventh graders. The victims suffered bruises and scrapes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/russia-kurgan-school-shooting/29112975.html|title=Russian Schoolgirl Shoots Classmates With Gas Pistol, Seven Injured |date=March 21, 2018 |work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 18, 2018}}\n|[[Sterlitamak]], Russia\n| Student\n|\n| 4 injured\n| Four people were hospitalized after a knife-wielding teenage student attacked his school in Russia's Bashkortostan region, in the city of Sterlitamak. The attacker wounded three girls and a teacher and set a classroom on fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/three-students-teacher-hospitalized-after-teen-attacks-school-in-russia/29174568.html|title=Three Students, Teacher Hospitalized After Teen Attacks School In Rus